  <discussion>Thamnobryum neckeroides is distinguished by the distinctly concave, almost boat-shaped branch leaves, and the rounded to broadly rounded apex. The apical laminal cells are mostly subquadrate to short-rhomboidal and the medial juxtacostal cells have their longest axis parallel to the costa.</discussion>
